image.altText: Former NRL player Jarryd Hayne looking unhappy in a street

items.synopsis: The former NRL player remarked "say no more" after the judge read out his sentence for the 2018 sexual assault in Newcastle.

title.children: 'Say no more': Jarryd Hayne sentenced to four years, nine months' jail for sexual assault

image.altText: Parliament House in Canberra

items.synopsis: Greens MPs and other crossbenchers could soon join parliament's high-powered intelligence committee under proposed government changes which the opposition warns will increase the risk of classified material leaking.

title.children: 'Grubby political deal': Security stoush over changes to parliament's intelligence committee

image.altText: A graphic image showing a zombie hand and a superannuation piggy bank.

items.synopsis: Australia's biggest superannuation fund reveals that it has been double charging some customers, and will refund around $70 million in fees and insurance costs to about 100,000 people.

title.children: AustralianSuper's 'alarming' $70m double-up on customer accounts sparks calls for wider probe

image.altText: a woman tied up and sitting on the floor

items.synopsis: Police know of four cases across NSW in the past month, with Chinese students as young as 17 targeted and ordered to pay sums of up to $280,000 or face being deported.

title.children: 'Virtual kidnapping' on the rise, as scammers 'prey' on Chinese international students in Sydney

image.altText: Peter Dutton sits in the House of Representatives

items.synopsis: The stately architecture of budget week follows a similar path each time, but this year it had the Dutton Button added in, writes Annabel Crabb.

title.children: It was all going to script. Then the opposition leader reached for the Dutton Button

image.altText: Imran Khan wears sunglasses as he is ushered through a crowd surrounded by armour-wearing police officers on city street

items.synopsis: A high court in Islamabad grants former prime minister Imran Khan a two-week reprieve from arrest in a corruption case and grants him bail on the charges, three days after he was taken into custody by Pakistan authorities.

title.children: Pakistan court releases former prime minister Imran Khan on two weeks' bail

image.altText: Close up of white man with curly blonde hair in a suit.

items.synopsis: The man who kept a chokehold around the neck of an agitated fellow passenger in the New York City subway, leading to the other rider's death, turns himself in to authorities.

title.children: Marine who fatally choked New York city subway rider Jordan Neely surrenders to police

image.altText: A plump man in a grey suit stand between two PNG flags as he speak from behind.

items.synopsis: PNG's foreign minister faced widespread calls to resign after he called critics of a video, made during a taxpayer-funded trip to the coronation of King Charles III and posted on social media by his daughter, "primitive animals" and "useless individuals".

title.children: Papua New Guinea's Foreign Minister Justin Tkatchenko steps aside

image.altText: Aerial photo of horses walking across a muddy bank and into water.

items.synopsis: The public service union says threats are escalating against National Parks and Wildlife rangers trying implement feral horse control programs in alpine NSW.

title.children: Threats against staff working in feral horse program force National Parks staff to wear body cameras

image.altText: Jana Stewart smiles while sitting in a parliamentary committee

items.synopsis: The committee has spent six weeks travelling the country holding hearings into the proposed wording. It wants the parliament to pass the referendum legislation without any changes.

title.children: Labor-led Voice committee backs referendum wording, Coalition dissents

image.altText: Machinery in a factory including two large silver vat-like parts.

items.synopsis: Bioelektra Australia has entered into voluntary administration after it was engaged to use Polish technology to divert 90 per cent of a NSW council's waste from landfill.

title.children: Calls for answers after recycling company that promised a 'revolution' collapses

image.altText: A sign that reads "Griffith Court House" out the front of a Federation-style brick building with columns at the entrance.

items.synopsis: Simon Carberry will be eligible for parole in 2026 after fatally stabbing Sayed Mousawi in Griffith, NSW, during what a judge described as an ill-conceived plan to steal the victim's car in 2020.

title.children: Man jailed over fatal stabbing during botched robbery triggered by text to girlfriend

image.altText: Lisa Wilkinson on stage at the 2022 Logie Awards.

items.synopsis: Media reports at the time claimed journalist Lisa Wilkinson had been given a clear direction from the ACT Director of Public Prosecutions not to give the speech, which her lawyer disputes.

title.children: ACT's top prosecutor admits he should have done more to correct media reporting of Lisa Wilkinson's Logies speech

image.altText: US Marines compete in a shooting competition in Darwin.

items.synopsis: An ex-US Marine bomb technician set alight in a barbecue explosion is claiming officials knew about a gas leak which led to the incident.

title.children: US Marine burned by exploding barbecue in Darwin sues US, Australian governments for millions

image.altText: Sam Kerr claps her hands and smiles

items.synopsis: Sam Kerr wins the award for a second-straight year, the first woman to do so, while Manchester City striker Erling Haaland caps his first season in the Premier League by claiming the men's award.

title.children: Sam Kerr wins back-to-back FWA player of the year prizes

image.altText: Reds players hug each other and smile

items.synopsis: It has been 10 years and 21 matches since the Reds won a Super Rugby match on New Zealand soil but they managed a 25-22 victory against the previously unbeaten ladder leaders, the Chiefs.

title.children: Reds end decade-long drought in Super Rugby Pacific boilover

image.altText: a dog sits beside a plaque

items.synopsis: More than 100 people, some travelling from overseas, are due to attend the festivities which will include plenty of local food and a dance troupe which Bobi will dance with.

title.children: World's oldest dog Bobi celebrates his 31st birthday

image.altText: a woman holding onto an empty cardboard box outside a food charity

items.synopsis: Food charities are struggling to keep their pantries stocked with more hungry mouths to feed than ever before, but there was no joy in this week's federal budget.

title.children: Glenda gets all her family's meals from a food bank, but no budget relief means many will miss out

image.altText: Louis Daniels walks next to a man wearing a suit.

items.synopsis: As former Tasmanian Anglican Priest Louis Victor Daniels is sentenced to six years in jail for the sexual abuse of two boys in the 1970s and 80s, one of them makes a plea for more abuse survivors to come forward.

title.children: Former Anglican priest Louis Daniels sentenced for 'heinous' sexual abuse of boys in Tasmania

image.altText: Police tape at a crime scene

items.synopsis: After initially pleading not guilty last year, 23-year-old Samuel Albert Campbell has pleaded guilty to murdering a man and wounding another with intent to cause grievous bodily harm in 2021.

title.children: Man pleads guilty to stabbing murder after altercation with two men on road outside Cooma

image.altText: Peter Hollingworth

items.synopsis: Former governor-general Peter Hollingworth says he has given up his permission to officiate as an Anglican priest, after a church investigation last month found he committed misconduct by knowingly allowing paedophiles to remain in the church.

title.children: Peter Hollingworth says he will no longer officiate as Anglican priest after church investigation finding

image.altText: John Pesutto and Moira Deeming in a composite image.

items.synopsis: Rebel Victorian MP Moira Deeming has been expelled from the parliamentary Liberal Party after a meeting of MPs this morning, with Renee Heath ditched as partyroom secretary.

title.children: Victorian Liberal leader labels expulsion of MP Moira Deeming a 'turning point' in party's reform

image.altText: Penrith Panthers players jump on each other in celebration next to the goalposts after a try against the Roosters.

items.synopsis: The Panthers flex their muscles with a big win over the Roosters, who lose a key player to injury, after the Warriors down a frustrated Bulldogs side to earn their sixth win of the season

title.children: Panthers run riot against Roosters, as the Warriors down the Bulldogs

image.altText: A female Aedes aegypti mosquito bites someone's skin.

items.synopsis: Health officials say there have now been four cases, inlcuding two fatal, of the disease this year in the Northern Territory compared to two cases in the previous five years.

title.children: Infant dies of Murray Valley encephalitis in NT, as officials issue warning following spike in cases

image.altText: An artist depiction of a yellow black hole with a streak of light through the middle and a blue orb in front.

items.synopsis: Astronomers have identified the "largest" cosmic explosion ever observed, a fireball 100 times the size of our Solar System that suddenly began blazing in the distant universe more than three years ago.

title.children: Two trillion times brighter than the Sun: 'Largest' cosmic explosion puzzles astronomers

image.altText: Lara Alexander and John Tucker looking at each other.

items.synopsis: Concerns over a contentious $715 million stadium and the government's priorities have pushed two Tasmanian MPs to quit the Liberal Party and sit as independents, ending Premier Jeremy Rockliff's majority.

title.children: Anger over Hobart AFL stadium sinks Tasmania's government into minority as MPs quit party

image.altText: People walk through the front door of a house, past a For Lease sign.

items.synopsis: Despite increased rental assistance measures in Tuesday's budget, calls to cap rents are growing louder, with economists saying that step has been successful overseas, however, analysts warn it may make the housing crisis worse.

title.children: 'We need intervention': Renters say price caps are needed to help keep a roof over their heads

image.altText: Domenic Perre pictured during the 1990s, with slicked back hair, a patterned blue shirt and aviator shades

items.synopsis: The family of Domenic Perre, who died earlier this week less than a year after he was convicted of murdering a detective in the 1994 NCA bombing, is considering making a petition for mercy.

title.children: Bomber's family considers posthumous mercy bid days after his death

image.altText: A patch of grey rock exposed on a green mountain with a village of houses at the bottom of the mountain

items.synopsis: Residents in the village of Brienz have been ordered to abandon their tiny mountain home.

title.children: Evacuation deadline looms for Swiss village at risk of being destroyed by a massive landslide

image.altText: A teenage girl in sports gear concentrates as she grasps and swings between two "X"-shaped plates hanging from the ceiling.

items.synopsis: Abbey Cutts has won the right to represent Australia in two international ninja championships in the United States next month. But first she has to get there.

title.children: Teenager Abbey Cutts practises for hours on a ninja course in her backyard. Now she's heading to world finals

image.altText: A close-up photograph of Ricardo Barbaro, a man with short dark hair and a neat beard.

items.synopsis: Ricardo Barbaro will face a third murder trial over the death of Melbourne woman Ellie Price after a jury was discharged to give lawyers time to examine new evidence.

title.children: Ellie Price murder trial abandoned for a second time after new evidence emerges

image.altText: Machinery in a factory including two large silver vat-like parts.

items.synopsis: Bioelektra Australia has entered into voluntary administration after it was engaged to use Polish technology to divert 90 per cent of a NSW council's waste from landfill.

title.children: Calls for answers after recycling company that promised a 'revolution' collapses

image.altText: Soldiers launch missiles hidden by camouflage tents and surrounded by trees

items.synopsis: Moscow reacts after Russian military bloggers report Ukrainian advances north and south of the fiercely contested city of Bakhmut in the east of Ukraine, while some US Senators accuse the Pentagon of undermining a war crimes probe by refusing to share information with the ICC.

title.children: Russia denies reports of Ukrainian breakthroughs along front lines near Bakhmut

image.altText: Short sleeved dark navy police t-shirt, viewed from back of officer in uniform

items.synopsis: Emergency services were contacted when a visiting relative attempted to see the man and was allegedly told he was in hospital.

title.children: 'Mummified' body found in Gold Coast home where two people lived

image.altText: Frank Hu holds a phone to his ear, dressed in a green jumper.

items.synopsis: A serial rapist will spend decades behind bars for spiking the drinks of female colleagues, sexually abusing them while they were passed out and posting images of the attacks online.

title.children: Man who offered female colleagues drugged drinks before raping them jailed for 'cold, calculated' attacks
